---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Container from '../components/ui/Container.astro';
import SectionHeader from '../components/ui/SectionHeader.astro';
import Button from '../components/ui/Button.astro';
---

<Layout title="MLL Lab â€” Join Us">
	<main class="bg-background-light py-12">
		<Container maxWidth="xl">
			<h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-heading font-bold text-secondary-900 text-center mb-12">Join us!</h1>
			
			<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
				<section class="mb-12 bg-white rounded-xl shadow-medium p-8">
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold text-secondary-900 mb-4">PhD Students</h2>
					<p class="text-secondary-700 mb-6">
						We welcome PhD students to join our lab! If you are interested, please apply to Northwestern CS (deadline: Dec 1st, but application will be open until Dec 15) and make sure to select <a href="https://limanling.github.io" class="text-primary-600 hover:underline">Manling Li</a> as your potential advisor in the application. Due to the high volume of inquiries, <b>individual emails will not be able to receive a response, but it does NOT mean we are not interested</b>. All applications will be carefully reviewed in late December, with interviews conducted from January to March.
					</p>
					<div class="flex justify-center md:justify-start">
						<Button 
							href="https://www.mccormick.northwestern.edu/computer-science/academics/graduate/phd/" 
							variant="outline" 
							target="_blank" 
							rel="noopener"
						>
							Why PhD @ NU (English)
						</Button> &nbsp;
						<Button 
							href="https://www.1point3acres.com/bbs/thread-1084711-1-1.html" 
							variant="outline" 
							target="_blank" 
							rel="noopener"
						>
							Why PhD @ NU (Chinese)
						</Button> &nbsp;
						<Button 
							href="https://www.mccormick.northwestern.edu/computer-science/academics/graduate/admissions/" 
							variant="outline" 
							target="_blank" 
							rel="noopener"
						>
							Apply Now
						</Button>
					</div>
				</section>
				
				<section class="mb-12 bg-white rounded-xl shadow-medium p-8">
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold text-secondary-900 mb-4">Research Internships</h2>
					<p class="text-secondary-700 mb-6">
						We welcome research interns in multiple formats! Please submit our application form. If you would like to drop an email, please send it to <a href="mailto:limanling.ai@gmail.com" class="text-primary-600 hover:underline">limanling.ai@gmail.com</a>. We encourage you to contact the PhD student directly if you are interested in collaborating with any of them, since we normally will have a PhD mentor for each research intern. Talking to PhD students are the most effective way to get started. 
					</p>
					<div class="flex justify-center md:justify-start">
						<Button 
							href="https://hackmd.io/@zAmnkcJDS5CHhVb-PzcMPA/S15pslRn0" 
							variant="primary" 
							target="_blank" 
							rel="noopener"
						>
						Prospective Students (English)
						</Button> &nbsp;
						<Button 
							href="https://hackmd.io/@zAmnkcJDS5CHhVb-PzcMPA/HyJyoQuhR" 
							variant="primary" 
							target="_blank" 
							rel="noopener"
						>
						Prospective Students (Chinese)
						</Button> &nbsp;
						<Button 
							href="https://forms.gle/unVqpW97bGwQsrRz5" 
							variant="primary" 
							target="_blank" 
							rel="noopener"
						>
							Form Submission
						</Button> &nbsp;
						
					</div>
				</section>
				
				<section class="mb-12 bg-white rounded-xl shadow-medium p-8">
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold text-secondary-900 mb-4">Northwestern Students</h2>
					<p class="text-secondary-700 mb-6">
						Students interested in joining the MLL Lab are also encouraged to do <b>independent study</b> (feel free to attent Manling's office hour on Monday morning 9:00-10:00 in Mudd 3201) or take our <b>CS_496 course (Agent AI / Large Agent Models)</b> or <b>CS_396 (Reasoning and Planning in Foundation Models)</b>.
						The course provides training on cutting-edge foundation models for agents. Course assignments involve building your own agent, giving you hands-on experience with the technologies we use in our research.
					</p>
					<div class="flex justify-center md:justify-start">
						<Button 
							href="https://limanling.github.io/#teaching" 
							variant="outline" 
							target="_blank" 
							rel="noopener"
						>
							Course Information
						</Button>
					</div>
				</section>
			</div>
		</Container>
	</main>
</Layout>
